  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-03-18", 
    "text": "Low-Income Housing Preservation Act of 1997 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to provide a 15-year recovery period for the depreciation deduction for new investments to rehabilitate qualified low-income housing projects. Exempts $50,000 ($25,000 in the case of a separate return by a married individual) of such rehabilitation costs from the passive loss limitations. Provides a special rule for computing the depreciation deduction for such housing projects."
